<body>
  <div class="container">
    <h1>Car Exhaust System Guide</h1>

    <!-- Purpose Section -->
    <div class="card">
      <h2>Purpose</h2>
      <p>The exhaust system is a critical component of a vehicle, designed to safely direct exhaust gases away from the engine and passengers. It also reduces noise, improves engine performance, and minimizes harmful emissions.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Components of the Exhaust System Section -->
    <div class="card">
      <h2>Components</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Exhaust Manifold:</strong> Collects exhaust gases from the engine cylinders and directs them into the exhaust pipe.</li>
        <li><strong>Catalytic Converter:</strong> Reduces harmful emissions by converting toxic gases into less harmful substances.</li>
        <li><strong>Muffler:</strong> Reduces noise produced by the exhaust gases as they exit the system.</li>
        <li><strong>Resonator:</strong> Works with the muffler to further reduce noise and improve exhaust flow.</li>
        <li><strong>Tailpipe:</strong> The final section of the exhaust system, directing gases out of the vehicle.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- How It Works Section -->
    <div class="card">
      <h2>How It Works</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Exhaust gases exit the engine through the exhaust manifold.</li>
        <li>The gases flow through the catalytic converter, where harmful emissions are reduced.</li>
        <li>The muffler and resonator dampen the noise produced by the exhaust gases.</li>
        <li>Finally, the gases exit the vehicle through the tailpipe.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Maintenance Section -->
    <div class="card">
      <h2>Maintenance</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Regularly inspect the exhaust system for rust, cracks, or holes and repair or replace damaged parts.</li>
        <li>Check the catalytic converter for clogs or damage, which can reduce engine performance.</li>
        <li>Listen for unusual noises (e.g., rattling or loud exhaust sounds) that may indicate a problem.</li>
        <li>Ensure the exhaust system is securely mounted to prevent vibrations and damage.</li>
        <li>Schedule periodic inspections to maintain the system's efficiency and performance.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Signs of Exhaust System Issues Section -->
    <div class="card">
      <h2>Signs of Exhaust System Issues</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Loud Exhaust Noise:</strong> A damaged muffler or exhaust pipe can cause excessive noise.</li>
        <li><strong>Reduced Fuel Efficiency:</strong> A clogged or malfunctioning exhaust system can reduce engine efficiency.</li>
        <li><strong>Unusual Smells:</strong> A rotten egg smell may indicate a failing catalytic converter.</li>
        <li><strong>Visible Damage:</strong> Rust, holes, or cracks in the exhaust system are clear signs of wear.</li>
        <li><strong>Check Engine Light:</strong> A malfunctioning exhaust system can trigger the check engine light.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

